Text: '
The cult centers of Apollo in Greece, '
Begin Reference: Delphi
End Reference: Delphi
Text: ' and '
Begin Reference: Delos
End Reference: Delos
Text: ', date from the 8th century BCE. The Delos sanctuary was primarily dedicated to '
Begin Reference: Artemis
End Reference: Artemis
Text: ', Apollo's twin sister. At Delphi, Apollo was venerated as the slayer of '
Begin Reference: Pytho
End Reference: Pytho
Text: '. For the Greeks, Apollo was all the Gods in one and through the centuries he acquired different functions which could originate from different gods. In '
Begin Reference: archaic period in Greece
k: null
Text: 'archaic Greece'
End Reference: archaic period in Greece
Text: ' he was the '
Begin Reference: prophet
End Reference: prophet
Text: ', the oracular god who in older times was connected with "healing". In '
Begin Reference: classical period in Greece
k: null
Text: 'classical Greece'
End Reference: classical period in Greece
Text: ' he was the god of light and of music, but in popular religion he had a strong function to keep away evil.'
Open Tag: ref attributes: []
Text: 'Martin Nilsson (1967)".Die Geschicte der Giechischen Religion.Vol I".C.F.Beck Verlag.Munchen. p 529'
