End Reference: omen
Text: '" (σημεία και τέρατα : '
ItalicBold: 2
Text: 'semeia kai terata'
ItalicBold: 2
Text: '), and of the observation of the '
Begin Reference: omen
End Reference: omen
Text: 's of the days. The inspiration oracular-cult was probably introduced from '
Begin Reference: Anatolia
End Reference: Anatolia
Text: '. The '
Begin Reference: ritualism
End Reference: ritualism
Text: ' belonged to Apollo from the beginning. The Greeks created the '
Begin Reference: Legalism (Western philosophy)
k: null
Text: 'legalism'
End Reference: Legalism (Western philosophy)
Text: ', the supervision of the orders of the gods, and the demand for moderation and harmony. Apollo became the god of shining youth, the protector of music, spiritual-life, moderation and perceptible order. The improvement of the old '
Begin Reference: Anatolia
End Reference: Anatolia
Text: 'n god, and his elevation to an intellectual sphere, may be considered an achievement of the '
Begin Reference: Greek people
k: null
Text: 'Greek'
End Reference: Greek people
Text: ' people.'
