Text: '
'
Begin Reference: Hyacinth (mythology)
k: null
Text: 'Hyacinth'
End Reference: Hyacinth (mythology)
Text: ' or Hyacinthus was one of Apollo's male lovers. He was a '
Begin Reference: Sparta
End Reference: Sparta
Text: 'n prince, beautiful and athletic. The pair was practicing throwing the '
Begin Reference: Discus throw
k: null
Text: 'discus'
End Reference: Discus throw
Text: ' when a discus thrown by Apollo was blown off course by the jealous '
Begin Reference: Zephyrus
End Reference: Zephyrus
Text: ' and struck Hyacinthus in the head, killing him instantly. Apollo is said to be filled with grief: out of Hyacinthus' blood, Apollo created a '
Begin Reference: hyacinth (plant)
k: null
Text: 'flower'
End Reference: hyacinth (plant)
Text: ' named after him as a memorial to his death, and his tears stained the flower petals with the interjection '
Begin Template: lang
