Text: ' The Festival of Hyacinthus was a celebration of Sparta.'
Paragraph
Text: 'Another male lover was '
Begin Reference: Cyparissus
End Reference: Cyparissus
Text: ', a descendant of '
Begin Reference: Heracles
End Reference: Heracles
Text: '. Apollo gave him a tame deer as a companion but Cyparissus accidentally killed it with a '
Begin Reference: Pilum
k: null
Text: 'javelin'
End Reference: Pilum
Text: ' as it lay asleep in the undergrowth. Cyparissus asked Apollo to let his tears fall forever. Apollo granted the request by turning him into the '
Begin Reference: Cupressaceae
k: null
Text: 'Cypress'
End Reference: Cupressaceae
Text: ' named after him, which was said to be a sad tree because the sap forms droplets like tears on the trunk.'
